.TH "pci_map_rom" 9 "pci_map_rom" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_map_rom \- map a PCI ROM to kernel space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __iomem *" pci_map_rom
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "size_t *size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
pointer to pci device struct
.IP "size" 12
pointer to receive size of pci window over ROM
.SH "RETURN"
kernel virtual pointer to image of ROM
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Map a PCI ROM into kernel space. If ROM is boot video ROM,
the shadow BIOS copy will be returned instead of the
actual ROM.
